<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Engine Electrical - Inspect and
        Test - Measure CMP Sensor Clearance
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210011104.3" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Measure CMP Sensor Clearance</title>
        <svcprocinfo id="s210011104.3.1">
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Use worksheet to complete CMP sensor air gap analysis to obtain correct CMP sensor
                        clearance.
                    </para>
                </note>
                <note>
                    <para>Use proper combination of shims to achieve the desired air gap of 0.635 to 0.762 mm (0.025 to
                        0.030 in).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="s210011104.3.2">
            <title>Determine CMP Sensor Clearance</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate crankshaft in clockwise direction (viewed from front) at least two revolutions.
                    Do not turn backwards.
                </para>
                <para>Install calibrated depth gage tool.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure distance from CMP sensor mounting surface to trigger wheel tooth.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>When making following measurement, measure up to tooth on trigger wheel. Do not measure
                            window between teeth.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate crankshaft clockwise (viewed from front) 1/2 turn. Repeat Step 2.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate crankshaft clockwise 1/2 turn. Repeat Step 2.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate crankshaft clockwise 1/2 turn. Repeat Step 2.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Add measurements from Steps 2 through 5. Total of 4 measurements.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Obtain average dimension by dividing sum obtained in step 6 by 4.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure CMP sensor length from tip to surface of mounting flange.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Determine CMP air gap, subtract Step 8 from Step 7.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Desired air gap: 0.635 to 0.762 mm (0.025 to 0.030 in)</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Determine CMP air gap interference, subtract Step 10 from Step 9.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Select shims as required from shim kit (two 1.5 mm (0.005 in) and two 3.0 mm (0.010 in)
                    shims provided). Use one or more shims from kit to get as close as possible to desired air gap in
                    Step 10. Measure thickness of shim(s).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place shims over CMP sensor tip. Make sure shims are centered on CMP sensor flange.
                    Install CMP sensor and shim assembly in front cover. Tighten clamp bolt to 20 N&#183;m (15 lbf&#183;ft)
                    and connect wiring harness.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <table id="t210011101" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>CMP Air Gap Analysis Worksheet</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="11.72*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="66.22*"/>
                    <colspec colname="COLSPEC0" colwidth="22.07*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>
                                    <title>Step</title>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <title>Operation</title>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <title>Measurement</title>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>2</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Record initial measured distance from CMP sensor mounting surface to trigger wheel
                                    tooth.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0"></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>3</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Record measured distance after crankshaft rotation.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0"></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>4</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Record measured distance after crankshaft rotation.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0"></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>5</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Record measured distance after crankshaft rotation.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0"></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>6 and 7</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Record average dimension.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0"></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>8</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Record CMP sensor length.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0"></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>9</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Record actual air gap.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0"></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>11</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Record CMP air gap interference between actual and desired air gap.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0"></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>12</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Enter measured shim pack thickness.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0"></entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s210011104.3.3">
            <title>Method One</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove CMP sensor mounting bolt from front cover and pull CMP sensor out. Clean sensor
                    mounting surface.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210011131" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5073.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Remove CMP Sensor</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Note part number on connector end of sensor (underside of sensor). Compare part number
                    to Calibration Chart. Calibrate using
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_285.xml" xrefid="t210011105">Camshaft Sensor Air Gap tool (ZTSE4414)
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <table id="t210011102" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Calibration Chart</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="49.50*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="50.50*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>C91</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                <para>1.152 / Red</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>C92</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                <para>1.142 / Blue</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert Camshaft Sensor Air Gap tool in calibration cup of selected color. Keep firm
                    downward pressure on tool and zero dial indicator.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten lock tab on dial ring. Tool is now calibrated for length of CMP sensor to be
                    installed in engine.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210011132" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8180.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Calibrate Camshaft Sensor Air Gap tool in calibration cup</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install Camshaft Sensor Air Gap tool in front cover and tighten clamp screw to 1.13 N&#183;m
                    (10 lbf&#183;in).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate engine with starter, or bar engine over by hand, for at least two complete
                    revolutions of crankshaft before observing any readings.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Observe needle sweep on dial indicator. Range sweep is an indication of timing wheel
                    runout, should be less than 0.20 mm (0.008 in).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210011133" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8178.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Measure CMP sensor clearance</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Crank engine long enough to get an average reading on dial indicator. If interference is
                    observed during cranking, CMP sensor may have been damaged and must be replaced.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install CMP sensor with required shims. Make sure that shims are centered on CMP sensor
                    flange. Use a small amount of grease to hold them, if necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect sensor wiring harness and test engine.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s210011104.3.4">
            <title>Method Two</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully measure the CMP sensor from tip to mounting flange with a
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_285.xml" xrefid="t210011105">Depth Micrometer</hotlnk>
                    or
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_285.xml" xrefid="t210011105">Precision Caliper</hotlnk>
                    . Record dimension in appropriate box on work sheet.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210011134" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5896.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Measure with depth micrometer</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Perform math as directed on work sheet. Then select appropriate combination of shims
                    from
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_285.xml" xrefid="t210011105">Shim Kit</hotlnk>
                    , if required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install CMP sensor with required shims. Make sure shims are centered on CMP sensor
                    flange. Use small amount of grease to hold them, if necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect sensor wiring harness and test engine.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
